review_blob:
33 Cl Bottle - Paris, France

I am one of the few who have actually tasted this beer straight from France itself. The stuff that they import to Canada is shit. But the actual local stuff is fantastic. A dark gold colour, with a nice white lasting head. Aroma of citrus, sweet flavor, with a semi-dry finish.  A fantastically crafted beer. Please dont give up on it just yet, head over to France and youll see what I mean ;)

341 ml Bottle

Fantastic. Simply put. Hands down my favorite beer to date.

Cloudy, Orange-Red colour, with a lasting off-white head. A nice, soft, whiskey taste on the palate, and then a powerful (yet not overpowering) malt finish. It retains its flavor right down to the bottom of the glass.  A wonderfully crafted beer, too bad they dont sell it where I live :(

341 ml Bottle

I was very impressed with this beer.  I thought it had a nice, inoffensive taste with a pleasant smell.  To be honest I couldnt pick out any particular flavors or aromas (Im embarrassed to say). But it was a tasty beer anyhow. Definitely going to go pick up some more of this lovely beer.

341 ml Bottle.

A disappointment. I picked up on the smell of corn and grain in the mix, as well as an unfortunate smell of cheap alcohol.  The taste was more bitter then I expected, with that returning cheap alcohol taste. Its really too bad considering its a 20th anniversary ale.

341 ml Bottle.

I was pleasantly surprised when I had this beer. I was expecting something so mass produced to be really shitty but it acctually wasnt that bad.  Nothing fantastic, but not bad. Taste of corn, a bit of hops, and a decent carbonation. Id  probably buy it again, but like I said, nothing special.

341 ml bottle.

Nothing special at all. A lot better then most mass produced beers, but still nothing great. Tastes of corn, a little hop, but not much. Lots of carbonation and a bitter aftertaste.Probably wouldnt have it again.

Bottle

The only reason I rate this one a 2.3 is because I really like it with a lime. Something about it brings out a nice smooth flavor. However the beer alone is not very good at all. Id probably rate it a 1.5 or so, maybe SLIGHTLY more, but not by much. A yellow pour with an almost non-existent head. A bit of skunky taste but not too much, a little bit of corn and grain as well. Again nothing special, but the drinkability increases dramatically when a lime is thrown into the mix.

330ml Bottle

A real disappointment. A real pissy yellow color, with a skunky taste. Nothing special at all, would NEVER buy it again.
UPDATED: JUN 13, 2009
UPDATED: JUL 2, 2010
UPDATED: JUN 11, 2009

341ml Bottle

To be completely Honest, I expect a bit more from Big Rock, especially for their Lager. But It wasnt too bad.  A little bit too bitter for my taste though.

341ml Bottle

A nice taste to it. Definitely another personal favorite from Big Rock.  Its a nice bitterness on the palate, but a softening taste prevails if you let it stay on your tongue for a second. A nutty taste will hit the back of your throat as well.

341ml Bottle

Definately setting a good standard for Wheat Ales.  A nice orange-y/honey taste with just a touch of bitterness in the finish. A classic Unfiltered White appearance.  Not my favorite Wheat ale, but its definately up there!
UPDATED: JUN 11, 2009

341 ml bottle.  Pours a classic orange/gold color with a quick white head. Nothing incredibly potent but tasty nonetheless. A slight taste of orange, but it really comes out when you acctually eat a slice of orange with it.  I would definately buy another pack of this beer.
UPDATED: JAN 27, 2009

330 ml bottle, served in a glass.

The traditional look of a white beer, with a lasting, white foamy head.  Starts off with a orange-y taste, then moves to a sweet honey flavor, and then finishes off with a hint of coriander. A lovely beer all around, and one your never going to forget!

Its probably one of the worst beers out there. The only reason I give it a 1, is because its slightly better then Molson Black Ice, which is my least favorite beer of all time.  Lucky has a very pissy taste, terrible clarity, and it smells very metallic and almost stale.

Lets say your stranded on an island.
You have all the necessary tools and machines to brew a perfectly good beer.  You have hops, and you have barley. So you start to brew. But instead of hops, you have shit, and instead of barley you have more shit.  The end result is Molson Black Ice.  I made the mistake of buying 18 cans (12 pack and a 6) for me and my buddies just because we wanted to get drunk. We wanted something half decent, so we figured we go by the testimonials on this site.  WHO THE FUCK WOULD EVER DRINK THIS BEER OUT OF CHOICE?!?!?!  Its disgusting! It has a pissy aroma and appearance, it tastes like a watered down Stella Artois, except with more piss in it.  Im sorry to sound so vulgar and immature but this "beer" acctually makes me angry.  I managed to choke down 5 of these that night, and i thought i was going to die.  Do yourselves a favor and dont ever buy this beer.

Not too bad.
I like the smooth flavor, nothing offensive. But I find it tastes a bit too much like molson Black Ice, Which i hate with a passion. But to be honest, its a little better then average. Id probably buy it again.
UPDATED: JUN 11, 2009

355 ml Can.  I must say Im a bit disappointed in Moosehead.  Piss yellow colour and the flavor follows. Again, I am a man who prefers Dark beers, however I thought this would at least meet my expectations in one way or another. I was wrong.

341 ml Bottle. A decent beer. The Flavor was nothing special, however inoffensive. It seems that people are upset that It isnt brewed to traditional IPA standards.  I dont know enough about beer to give my own opinion on that subject, however, IPA or not...I liked. I would definately have a few of these in my fridge at all times.
The ONLY way I would EVER drink this beer again...Is if It was the only Beer in the bar and I really wanted a brew.  And even then I would be reluctant.

I was very egar to try this beer.  However I was majorly disapointed.  Seemed like a very strange beer.  Bitter, light in color, and did NOT meet my expectations.  Seems like it gets a bit too much praise for what its really worth.

I truly Enjoyed this beer. The first time I tried it was In the summer with my grandfather.  It was a very tasty beer with a fine aroma.  It was not too light, and not too dark (however to me there is no such thing as too dark).  I would recommend this to anyone who has brains.  500 ml Bottle
